          {
            "icon": "Star",
            "title": {
              "zh": "What Is French Terry Fabric?",
              "en": "What Is French Terry Fabric?"
            },
            "description": {
              "zh": "French terry is a knitted cotton fabric featuring a smooth outer surface and looped interior construction. Unlike brushed fleece, French terry provides improved breathability, lighter softness, and a more structured drape, making it highly popular in oversized streetwear hoodies and luxury casualwear. \n\nHeavyweight French terry fabric is engineered using loopback knitting techniques that create a textured inner surface while maintaining a smooth exterior. This construction improves airflow, moisture balance, and shape retention for premium oversized garments.",
              "en": "French terry is a knitted cotton fabric featuring a smooth outer surface and looped interior construction. Unlike brushed fleece, French terry provides improved breathability, lighter softness, and a more structured drape, making it highly popular in oversized streetwear hoodies and luxury casualwear. \n\nHeavyweight French terry fabric is engineered using loopback knitting techniques that create a textured inner surface while maintaining a smooth exterior. This construction improves airflow, moisture balance, and shape retention for premium oversized garments."
            }
          },
          {
            "icon": "Star",
            "title": {
              "zh": "Why Streetwear Brands Prefer French Terry",
              "en": "Why Streetwear Brands Prefer French Terry"
            },
            "description": {
              "zh": "Many premium streetwear brands choose French terry fabric for oversized hoodies because it creates a cleaner silhouette, improved drape, and a more structured luxury feel without excessive bulk.\n\nFrench terry has become a core fabric in luxury streetwear due to its ability to combine heavyweight structure with breathable comfort, making it ideal for oversized silhouettes, garment dye treatments, and vintage wash finishes.",
              "en": "Many premium streetwear brands choose French terry fabric for oversized hoodies because it creates a cleaner silhouette, improved drape, and a more structured luxury feel without excessive bulk.\n\nFrench terry has become a core fabric in luxury streetwear due to its ability to combine heavyweight structure with breathable comfort, making it ideal for oversized silhouettes, garment dye treatments, and vintage wash finishes."
            }
          },
          {
            "icon": "Star",
            "title": {
              "zh": "French Terry vs Fleece",
              "en": "French Terry vs Fleece"
            },
            "description": {
              "zh": "Compared to brushed fleece, French terry fabric offers better breathability and a cleaner oversized drape, while fleece provides additional warmth and softness. Both fabrics are widely used in heavyweight streetwear hoodies depending on the desired fit and finish.\n\nFrench terry is often preferred for premium oversized hoodies because it feels less bulky than fleece while maintaining structure and shape retention for modern streetwear silhouettes.",
              "en": "Compared to brushed fleece, French terry fabric offers better breathability and a cleaner oversized drape, while fleece provides additional warmth and softness. Both fabrics are widely used in heavyweight streetwear hoodies depending on the desired fit and finish.\n\nFrench terry is often preferred for premium oversized hoodies because it feels less bulky than fleece while maintaining structure and shape retention for modern streetwear silhouettes."
            }
          },
          {
            "icon": "Star",
            "title": {
              "zh": "French Terry Fabric Construction",
              "en": "French Terry Fabric Construction"
            },
            "description": {
              "zh": "Our heavyweight French terry fabrics are developed using compact cotton yarns and high-density knitting techniques to improve durability, reduce shrinkage, and enhance fabric recovery after washing.\n\nFrench terry fabric works exceptionally well with garment dye and vintage wash treatments due to its textured loopback interior and stable heavyweight construction.",
              "en": "Our heavyweight French terry fabrics are developed using compact cotton yarns and high-density knitting techniques to improve durability, reduce shrinkage, and enhance fabric recovery after washing.\n\nFrench terry fabric works exceptionally well with garment dye and vintage wash treatments due to its textured loopback interior and stable heavyweight construction."
            }
          }
